list.name: Default
list.comment: Finally able to recompile using Android 3.4.1. For some reason a TON of .java files were missing and the project failed to compile. Was able to reinsert missing files from backups. Will now see how the operation has changed from this current version to the newest API (28).

task.summary: Updated to Android Studio 1.3.0 and it lost the GIT settings so its going to be seen as yet another complete rebaseline. On the bright side, we were able to complete the delete day within the Calendar as well as fixing some dialog issues within the Utilities activity to ensure that the dialog doesn't loose its status if either the screen is rotated or the the app is stopped in the background and restarted.

Fixed issued (hopefully) with the utilities dialog being able to be closed by clicking away from the dialog, as we don't want this to happen while we are notifying the user that we are updating the progress on either backup/restore. We are also starting to do the copy as well and haven't really tested it yet, but will.

Fixed issue of not accounting for apostrophes in the Movement strings as they are passed to the database, as it was choking pretty hard on it. The Comments are already taken care of, as we need to put any apostrophe we see in as a double apostrophe. Now we can have those in the Movement titles as well.

On the binge of fixing apsotrophes. In the copy movement task in the DataBaseHelper, finally got it all working and only needed the replacement of apostrophes as double (otherwise the sql statement chokes), in addition to properly placing the apostrophes for all string/text values. The copy movement works properly now.

Fixed the one issue of not having the Dynamic come up when editing a movement container. Was also notified by Android Studio to no use "" to cocactonate my number only strings when I'm setting the TextView. I first put them in .toString, but it still complained that this did not take into account any locale differences in the off chance that I really push this application to the Play Store. Used the NumberFormat class to help with the locale items, and apparently this works.

Had to pull the source code from the roomarama for Caldroid and resync all my changes by hand. There has to be an easier way to examing the code and see the differences, but they are not very easily done when I saved the new code over the old and tried to view the changes manually via Github. In the future, I should save the two files and run a compare to see the differences.
